EICHER MOTORS: 

CO ROYAL ENFIELD EXPANDS 2026 HUNTER 350 LINEUP WITH NEW BASE PREMIUM VARIANT AND COLOURWAYS; 

BOOKINGS BEGIN APRIL 4, 2026; NEW FEATURES INCLUDE ALLOY WHEELS AND SINGLE-CHANNEL ABS.

UNION BANK OF INDIA: 

CO TOTAL GROSS ADVANCES INCREASED BY 9.76% YOY AS OF 31ST MARCH 2026; 

DOMESTIC ADVANCES UP 10.06% YOY; RAM ADVANCES GROWTH AT 12.59% YOY; 

DOMESTIC CASA DEPOSITS RISE BY 7.90% YOY.

BAJAJ AUTO: 

CO MARCH 2026 SALES REPORT RELEASED; DOMESTIC 2-WHEELER SALES UP 20% YOY;

EXPORTS INCREASED BY 21%; TOTAL SALES REACHED 4,45,377 UNITS, A 20% GROWTH YOY.

ESCORTS KUBOTA: 

CO TO INCREASE PRICES OF TRACTORS (EXCLUDING KUBOTA BRAND) EFFECTIVE APRIL 15, 2026; 

PRICE INCREASE WILL VARY BY MODEL AND GEOGRAPHY.

OLA ELECTRIC MOBILITY: 

CO SECURES PLI CERTIFICATION FOR ROADSTER X+ 4.5 KWH; 

FIRST MOTORCYCLE IN ROADSTER PORTFOLIO TO RECEIVE CERTIFICATION; 

CONFIRMS DVA COMPLIANCE FOR INCENTIVES UNDER PLI-AUTO SCHEME.

S H KELKAR AND COMPANY: 

CO Q4 FY 2025-26 REVENUES REACH ₹2,355 CRORE, UP 11.5% YOY; 

NET DEBT AT ₹789 CRORE; STABLE GROSS MARGINS DESPITE INFLATIONARY PRESSURES.

HINDUSTAN COPPER: 

CO. ACHIEVES PROVISIONAL SALES OF 27,367 TONNES OF METAL-IN-CONCENTRATE FOR FY 2025-26; 

SALES UP 12% COMPARED TO LAST YEAR.

SURYODAY SMALL FINANCE BANK: 

CO Q4 FY26 GROSS ADVANCES AT ₹13,201 CRORE, UP 29% Y-O-Y; 

DISBURSEMENTS GROW 46% Y-O-Y TO ₹3,077 CRORE; 

TOTAL DEPOSITS INCREASE 32% Y-O-Y TO ₹13,958 CRORE; CASA RISES 42% Y-O-Y TO ₹3,141 CRORE.

MOIL: 

CO. INCREASES PRICES OF MANGANESE ORE GRADES EFFECTIVE FROM 01.04.2026; 

FERRO GRADES WITH MN-44% AND ABOVE UP BY 15%; 

OTHER FERRO GRADES BELOW MN-44% UP BY 17.5%; 

SMGR AND CHEMICAL GRADES ALSO UP BY 17.5%; BASIC PRICE OF EMD MAINTAINED AT ₹1,80,000 PMT.

NOCIL: 

CO. STARTS TRIAL BATCHES FOR CAPACITY ENHANCEMENT IN RUBBER CHEMICALS AT DAHEJ; 

CAPITAL EXPENDITURE NOT EXCEEDING ₹250 CRORE; 

SAMPLES TO BE SENT TO CUSTOMERS FOR APPROVAL.

BOROSIL: 

CO PRODUCTION OPERATIONS FULLY RESTORED AT BOROSILICATE GLASS AND OPAL GLASS FURNACES; 

SECURED LPG SUPPLIES FROM OMCS AFTER FORCE MAJEURE IMPACT.

BANK OF BARODA: 

CO GLOBAL BUSINESS GROWS BY 13.93% YOY TO ₹30.79 TRILLION AS OF MARCH 31, 2026; 

GLOBAL ADVANCES INCREASE BY 16.23% YOY TO ₹14.30 TRILLION; GLOBAL DEPOSITS RISE BY 12.00% YOY TO ₹16.49 TRILLION

JASH ENGINEERING: 

CO. ACQUIRES 100% STAKE IN PENSTOCKS (UK) LIMITED FOR £550,000; 

ACQUISITION TO ESTABLISH PAN UK PRESENCE AND SUPPORT CLIENTELE IN WATER UTILITIES.

L&T FINANCE: 

CO REPORTS RETAIL DISBURSEMENTS OF ~₹24,080 CRORES FOR Q4 FY26, UP 62% Y-O-Y; 

FULL YEAR DISBURSEMENTS ESTIMATED AT ~₹83,190 CRORES, UP 39% Y-O-Y; 

RETAIL LOAN BOOK GROWS TO ~₹1,19,550 CRORES, UP 26% Y-O-Y.

PRESTIGE ESTATES PROJECTS LIMITED: 

CO LAUNCHES MEGA 5,120-UNIT TOWNSHIP 'PRESTIGE GOLDEN GROVE' IN HYDERABAD WITH GDV OF ₹9,500 CR; 

PROJECT SPREAD ACROSS 28.6 ACRES WITH TOTAL SALEABLE AREA OF ~10.36 MILLION SQ FT

VEDANTA LTD: 

CO ANNOUNCES RECORD PRODUCTION NUMBERS FOR Q4 AND FY26; 

HIGHEST EVER ANNUAL ALUMINIUM AND ALUMINA PRODUCTION; 

RECORD MINED METAL PRODUCTION AT ZINC INDIA; Q4 SILVER PRODUCTION UP 11% QOQ; POWER SALES INCREASED 43% YOY.

KERNEX MICROSYSTEMS (INDIA): 

CO. ANNOUNCES STRATEGIC PARTNERSHIP WITH A LEADING TECH FIRM TO ENHANCE PRODUCT OFFERINGS; 

FOCUS ON INNOVATION AND MARKET EXPANSION.

SENORES PHARMACEUTICALS: 

CO ANNOUNCES STRATEGIC JOINT VENTURE IN THE U.S. FOR FEDERAL AND DEFENSE SECTOR SUPPLIES; 

JV ENTITY NAMED AMERISYN, LLC FOR GOVERNMENT PROCUREMENT MARKET.

CFF FLUID CONTROL: 

CO BAGS ₹14.14 CR INDIAN NAVY EQUIPMENT PROCUREMENT ORDER FROM MATERIAL ORGANISATION; 

EXECUTION BY MARCH 2027

DHRUV CONSULTANCY SERVICES LTD: 

CO. EMPANELED AS PROJECT MANAGEMENT CONSULTANT FOR BRIHANMUMBAI MUNICIPAL CORPORATION; 

CONTRACT FOR DESIGN OF MUNICIPAL ROADS AND QUALITY ASSURANCE FOR FIVE YEARS.
